WEBVTT

00:01.208 --> 00:03.208
I'm here to tell you you're
backing the hell off my firm.

00:03.210 --> 00:04.209
You got to sign something

00:04.211 --> 00:05.543
saying that I had nothing to do
with this.

00:05.545 --> 00:07.379
- I already did.
- It's on you now.

00:07.381 --> 00:08.580
You want to see a copy
of the pictures

00:08.582 --> 00:11.149
your fiancée sent me?
- She didn't send you anything.

00:11.151 --> 00:13.318
I made copies, one for each
guy in the joint.

00:13.320 --> 00:14.319
Ah!

00:14.321 --> 00:15.320
Happy anniversary.

00:15.322 --> 00:17.155
It's so nice to be with a man

00:17.157 --> 00:18.456
who's so thoughtful
after spending all day

00:18.458 --> 00:20.458
with a man who doesn't even
know what the word means.

00:20.460 --> 00:21.459
Talking about Harvey.

00:21.461 --> 00:23.328
If you can't even separate
yourself from him

00:23.330 --> 00:25.130
when he's asking you to leave
a job that you love,

00:25.132 --> 00:26.631
makes me wonder if it's really
the job you love after all.

00:26.633 --> 00:28.299
I was thinking maybe
some of that money

00:28.301 --> 00:29.300
might go to your daughter.

00:29.302 --> 00:30.402
I know you don't talk to her.

00:30.404 --> 00:32.637
If you're playing with me
on this thing--

00:32.639 --> 00:34.272
I'm not playing you, Frank.

00:34.274 --> 00:36.041
What the hell are you doing
with Frank Gallo?

00:36.043 --> 00:37.042
Does Rachel know about this?

00:37.044 --> 00:38.176
- No.
- And you better hope

00:38.178 --> 00:39.377
Gallo doesn't leave her
a message

00:39.379 --> 00:40.645
the same way he left me one.

00:40.647 --> 00:42.080
Alex has a gun to his head.

00:42.082 --> 00:43.448
I have a way out of it,
but there's gonna be

00:43.450 --> 00:44.616
some consequences for Mike.

00:44.618 --> 00:46.518
Harvey, is there any other way
out of this mess?

00:46.520 --> 00:48.253
If there were, I wouldn't be
standing here.

00:48.255 --> 00:49.454
You think signing
Reform Corps.

00:49.456 --> 00:50.455
is gonna make this go away,

00:50.457 --> 00:51.456
they have something on him.

00:51.458 --> 00:53.091
Why don't you take the night
and decide

00:53.093 --> 00:55.293
if you trust me enough to keep
working here or not.

00:55.295 --> 00:56.327
The guard gave me a letter,

00:56.329 --> 00:58.129
and that guard was murdered
by an inmate.

00:58.131 --> 00:59.464
- You covered up a murder?
- They set me up.

00:59.466 --> 01:01.132
I'm not asking you to let it go;

01:01.134 --> 01:02.974
I'm telling you what would
happen if you don't.

01:04.337 --> 01:08.573
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:08.575 --> 01:12.610
<i>[phone line trilling]</i>

01:12.612 --> 01:18.416
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:18.418 --> 01:21.319
- I'm sorry, who's this?
- I get it.

01:21.321 --> 01:23.188
I haven't returned your calls
for a few days.

01:23.190 --> 01:26.458
- Now that you mention it--
- Listen, I'm sorry.

01:26.460 --> 01:28.359
I've been totally under
the gun at the office,

01:28.361 --> 01:30.495
but I think we're
out of the woods.

01:30.497 --> 01:32.197
Then how about
you make it up to me

01:32.199 --> 01:33.298
by letting me take you
out to dinner?

01:33.300 --> 01:34.532
<i>Thursday night.</i>

01:34.534 --> 01:36.334
Let me get this straight.

01:36.336 --> 01:37.869
I get caught up with work

01:37.871 --> 01:39.871
and my punishment is
you taking me out.

01:39.873 --> 01:41.372
I'm British, Harvey.

01:41.374 --> 01:43.108
We do things differently
across the pond.

01:43.110 --> 01:44.542
Then I guess I'll
see you Thursday.

01:44.544 --> 01:46.578
I guess you will.
Good night, Harvey.

01:46.580 --> 01:49.180
<i>Good night, Paula.</i>

01:49.182 --> 01:56.254
<i>♪ ♪</i>

