02:12.272 --> 02:15.206
<i>[phone line trilling]</i>

02:15.208 --> 02:17.909
<i>- Hello?</i>
- Mark, hi.

02:17.911 --> 02:19.677
It's Donna Paulson.

02:19.679 --> 02:21.646
Donna.

02:21.648 --> 02:25.483
Wow. It's, uh...

02:25.485 --> 02:26.551
good to hear from you.

02:26.553 --> 02:27.719
It's been a long time.

02:27.721 --> 02:30.622
Yeah. I was, um--

02:30.624 --> 02:35.593
I was just thinking about you
and I...

02:35.595 --> 02:37.495
decided
to give you a call.

02:37.497 --> 02:39.297
<i>I'm--I'm glad you did.</i>
<i>You know,</i>

02:39.299 --> 02:43.234
I think about you
from time to time, too.

02:43.236 --> 02:45.303
- This is weird.
<i>- Oh, I don't know.</i>

02:45.305 --> 02:49.340
Ex-girlfriend calling,
out of the blue, late night.

02:49.342 --> 02:51.476
<i>I think I've seen weirder.</i>
- Oh, have you.

02:51.478 --> 02:52.644
<i>Well, nothing I can think of</i>
<i>this second,</i>

02:52.646 --> 02:54.479
but I'm sure I have.

02:54.481 --> 02:56.381
<i>Well, while you're</i>
<i>thinking about it,</i>

02:56.383 --> 02:58.383
why don't you
check your calendar

02:58.385 --> 03:00.952
and see if you can squeeze me
in for lunch sometime soon.

03:00.954 --> 03:02.587
I don't have to
check my calendar.

03:02.589 --> 03:05.623
I'm pretty sure I can
squeeze you in any time.

03:05.625 --> 03:08.626
- Then how's tomorrow?
- Tomorrow sounds good.

03:08.628 --> 03:11.329
The, uh, place with the thing
by the thing?

03:11.331 --> 03:14.299
The place with the thing
by the thing sounds good.

03:14.301 --> 03:15.767
<i>See you there.</i>

03:15.769 --> 03:18.636
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:20.740 --> 03:22.473
[sighs]

03:24.477 --> 03:25.643
What are you doing here?

03:25.645 --> 03:27.278
I told you to take the night.

03:27.280 --> 03:28.580
I don't need
to take the night.

03:28.582 --> 03:30.481
I need to talk to you
right now.

03:30.483 --> 03:32.383
If you're here to tell me
to drop Reform Corp.,

03:32.385 --> 03:34.619
you've wasted a trip--
- I'm not here for that, Harvey.

03:34.621 --> 03:35.987
Alex told me everything.

03:35.989 --> 03:38.556
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

03:38.558 --> 03:40.825
Prove it.

03:40.827 --> 03:44.762
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:44.764 --> 03:46.731
I swear to God, if you're gonna
use this against him--

03:46.733 --> 03:48.433
I don't wanna use
anything against him.

03:48.435 --> 03:49.767
I wanna help him.
- Bullshit.

03:49.769 --> 03:52.737
It's not bullshit.
I listened to his story.

03:52.739 --> 03:54.772
Anyone could've found themselves
in that position.

03:54.774 --> 03:56.808
- So what are you saying?
- I'm saying that you and I

03:56.810 --> 03:59.677
are supposed to be
Batman and Robin, we--

03:59.679 --> 04:01.679
If we can't stop these guys
from getting away with it

04:01.681 --> 04:03.381
and save Alex in the meantime,

04:03.383 --> 04:04.582
then what the hell
are we doing?

04:04.584 --> 04:06.584
I'm guessing you got a plan.

04:06.586 --> 04:09.387
I'm guessing I do.

04:09.389 --> 04:11.522
You think we need to find
our Commissioner Gordon.

04:11.524 --> 04:13.591
- How'd you know that?
- Because I know Batman.

04:13.593 --> 04:15.693
And I know that he needs
someone on the inside

04:15.695 --> 04:17.495
who's working with him
behind the scenes.

04:17.497 --> 04:19.731
Look at you.
You do know Batman.

04:19.733 --> 04:21.599
- You got someone in mind?
- Of course I do.

04:21.601 --> 04:23.368
Unless you're
even dumber than you look,

04:23.370 --> 04:24.836
it's the same person
you're thinking of.

04:24.838 --> 04:29.774
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:32.612 --> 04:35.313
Robert, you have a minute?

04:35.315 --> 04:37.548
I got a minute to find out
how you got into my house.

04:37.550 --> 04:39.350
Laura let me in.

04:39.352 --> 04:41.286
Yeah, of course she did.

04:41.288 --> 04:44.355
She's under the misguided
impression that you're charming.

04:44.357 --> 04:47.392
Now why don't you tell me
what you got in that box.

04:47.394 --> 04:49.594
Just some files.
We were running out of space

04:49.596 --> 04:52.430
over at my firm and I thought
maybe I could just

04:52.432 --> 04:54.299
store them with you.
- [chuckles]

04:54.301 --> 04:56.501
You think I didn't
hear about that class action?

04:56.503 --> 04:58.469
Just about cracked
your firm in two?

04:58.471 --> 05:00.505
Why the hell would I touch that
with a ten foot pole?

05:00.507 --> 05:02.307
Robert, I don't have
a leg to stand on

05:02.309 --> 05:04.075
other than to say
that Mike took this on

05:04.077 --> 05:05.743
and found some bad shit.

05:05.745 --> 05:07.412
I'm giving you an opportunity
to right some wrongs,

05:07.414 --> 05:08.846
make a shitload of money

05:08.848 --> 05:11.883
and all you have to do
is show up for one meeting.

05:11.885 --> 05:14.819
I think I might have
some extra storage space here.

05:14.821 --> 05:16.854
But, Harvey, if you
leave that thing with me,

05:16.856 --> 05:19.657
the case is mine
and I run it how I see fit.

05:19.659 --> 05:22.660
- Is that a threat?
- Maybe it is, maybe it isn't.

05:22.662 --> 05:24.796
But once we step into that ring,

05:24.798 --> 05:26.764
I don't give a shit
who you are,

05:26.766 --> 05:28.533
I'm not pulling my punches.

05:28.535 --> 05:30.101
I wouldn't have it
any other way.

05:30.103 --> 05:34.605
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:35.768 --> 05:39.203
<i>♪ See the money,</i>
<i>wanna stay for your meal ♪</i>

05:39.205 --> 05:42.673
<i>♪ Get another piece of pie</i>
<i>for your wife ♪</i>

05:42.675 --> 05:45.809
<i>♪ Everybody wanna know</i>
<i>how it feel ♪</i>

05:45.811 --> 05:49.646
<i>♪ Everybody wanna see</i>
<i>what it's like ♪</i>

05:49.648 --> 05:52.549
<i>♪ I'll even eat a bean pie,</i>
<i>I don't mind ♪</i>

05:52.551 --> 05:56.520
<i>♪ Me and Missy is so busy,</i>
<i>busy making money ♪</i>

05:56.522 --> 05:58.021
<i>♪ All right ♪</i>

05:58.023 --> 05:59.260
<i>♪ All step back,</i>
<i>I'm 'bout to dance ♪</i>

05:59.261 --> 06:03.261
