06:09.576 --> 06:12.643
What the hell?
I thought you were on my side.

06:12.645 --> 06:14.178
- I am on your side.
- Then why did Robert Zane

06:14.180 --> 06:15.947
just come out of nowhere
and all of a sudden

06:15.949 --> 06:17.515
reopen that God damn case?
- Alex, relax.

06:17.517 --> 06:18.950
He didn't open it up
against your client;

06:18.952 --> 06:20.051
he opened it up
against Harvey's.

06:20.053 --> 06:21.652
What good does that do?

06:21.654 --> 06:23.187
They're in this thing together
and so am I.

06:23.189 --> 06:25.056
Listen to me. You've trusted
me with the truth.

06:25.058 --> 06:27.058
I gave you my word that I
wouldn't let you go down

06:27.060 --> 06:29.594
for something you didn't do.
- Well I guess your word is shit

06:29.596 --> 06:31.529
because the second
this trial starts,

06:31.531 --> 06:33.498
it's only a matter of time
till I've got a bull's-eye

06:33.500 --> 06:35.066
on my back.
- Well, then I guess

06:35.068 --> 06:37.835
it's a good thing there isn't
gonna be a trial.

06:37.837 --> 06:40.171
What are you talking about?

06:40.173 --> 06:42.006
I can't tell you
everything that's going on,

06:42.008 --> 06:43.608
but all you need to do
is make sure

06:43.610 --> 06:46.511
Masterson Construction
stands down.

06:46.513 --> 06:47.945
After that, you just
sit back and watch

06:47.947 --> 06:48.946
this whole thing go away.

06:48.948 --> 06:53.184
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:55.054 --> 06:56.954
God damn it!

06:59.125 --> 07:00.558
God damn it, Gretchen,

07:00.560 --> 07:01.893
I asked you for those
applications

07:01.895 --> 07:03.227
to replace
Stephanie days ago.

07:03.229 --> 07:05.096
Where the hell--
- I have them right here.

07:05.098 --> 07:06.597
Well, why didn't you
give them to me?

07:06.599 --> 07:08.566
Because there was
a problem--

07:08.568 --> 07:11.269
Wait a second, wait a second,
wait a second, wait a second.

07:11.271 --> 07:14.105
This doesn't feel right.
- How can you know that?

07:14.107 --> 07:15.273
Because when it comes
to applications,

07:15.275 --> 07:16.541
I'm like Rain Man
and this pile

07:16.543 --> 07:18.075
feels one applicant light.

07:18.077 --> 07:19.977
That's because
Columbia University

07:19.979 --> 07:21.646
chose not to send an applicant.

07:21.648 --> 07:23.214
Well, why the hell
didn't you tell me?

07:23.216 --> 07:25.283
Because it's one position.
We have applications

07:25.285 --> 07:28.886
from 19 of the top 20 schools,
you fool.

07:28.888 --> 07:31.222
- Did you just call me a fool?
- I call 'em like I see 'em.

07:31.224 --> 07:33.190
Well, I don't give a shit
about the other 19

07:33.192 --> 07:35.126
if there's even one that thinks
we're still

07:35.128 --> 07:36.561
not good enough
after Mike Ross.

07:36.563 --> 07:38.162
I'm not gonna let it stand.

07:38.164 --> 07:39.664
Louis, if you go over there
and make trouble,

07:39.666 --> 07:41.265
it won't only be
Columbia

07:41.267 --> 07:42.600
withholding lawyers from us,
it'll be every

07:42.602 --> 07:44.268
damn school in the country.

07:44.270 --> 07:46.137
Gretchen, if you're gonna keep
talking, you might as well

07:46.139 --> 07:47.605
say it to my ass 'cause I'm
going over there right now

07:47.607 --> 07:49.006
to let them know
who's too good for who.

07:49.008 --> 07:52.143
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:52.145 --> 07:53.911
[sighs]

07:53.913 --> 07:55.580
- Roger.
- What the hell?

07:55.582 --> 07:57.081
- What the hell, what?
- Don't give me that.

07:57.083 --> 07:58.716
I did a little digging.

07:58.718 --> 08:01.018
Robert Zane is about
to be Mike Ross' father-in-law

08:01.020 --> 08:02.620
and I don't think
it's a coincidence

08:02.622 --> 08:03.721
that all of a sudden,
he's coming after us

08:03.723 --> 08:05.723
on the exact same case.

08:05.725 --> 08:07.158
Roger, I'll take care of it.

08:07.160 --> 08:08.926
You better take care of it,
Harvey.

08:08.928 --> 08:10.194
Because I only signed with you

08:10.196 --> 08:13.064
because you promised to stop
Mike Ross,

08:13.066 --> 08:14.699
and I don't think
I have to remind you

08:14.701 --> 08:16.300
that if Reform Corp.
goes down,

08:16.302 --> 08:17.969
Alex Williams goes down

08:17.971 --> 08:20.271
and he takes
your whole damn firm with him.

08:20.273 --> 08:22.073
I told you.
I'll take care of it.

08:22.075 --> 08:24.075
But you're gonna need to do
something for me.

08:24.077 --> 08:26.377
- And what is that?
- Open your God damn checkbook.

08:26.379 --> 08:29.046
Robert, there's no cause
for you to talk

08:29.048 --> 08:30.715
to my client like that.
- Well, if you want me

08:30.717 --> 08:32.683
to invite him
to afternoon tea, I will.

08:32.684 --> 08:34.986
But if he wants this case to go
away, this is how much

08:34.988 --> 08:37.154
he's gonna have to pay.

08:38.157 --> 08:40.057
Are you out of your mind?

08:40.058 --> 08:41.325
Robert, this isn't
a settlement offer.

08:41.327 --> 08:43.193
This is a declaration of war.

08:43.196 --> 08:45.062
Then let's go to war.

08:45.064 --> 08:46.330
You think I'm afraid to put this
in front of a jury?

08:46.332 --> 08:48.232
You won't get near a jury

08:48.234 --> 08:50.101
'cause I'm gonna make sure
they know Mike Ross

08:50.103 --> 08:53.070
handed you this case
on a silver platter.

08:53.072 --> 08:54.672
And you don't have
the proof of that

08:54.674 --> 08:56.407
or you wouldn't be
at a settlement meeting.

08:56.409 --> 08:58.643
But I do have the proof
that you not only schemed

08:58.645 --> 09:02.079
to extend sentences, but
murdered someone to cover it up.

09:02.081 --> 09:04.081
- What are you talking about?
- I'm talking about the fact

09:04.083 --> 09:07.418
that I have an eyewitness in
prison who'll testify in court.

09:07.420 --> 09:09.220
And who is this witness?

09:09.222 --> 09:10.354
You know who he is.

09:10.356 --> 09:12.690
And he knows who you are.

09:12.692 --> 09:14.392
And unless you take my deal,

09:14.394 --> 09:17.662
you're gonna end up
behind bars yourself.

09:20.333 --> 09:22.667
I am not paying
that kind of money

09:22.669 --> 09:24.435
and I am not admitting
to anything.

09:24.437 --> 09:28.372
Roger, you heard him.
He has a witness.

09:28.374 --> 09:29.707
Then you better make sure
Frank Gallo

09:29.709 --> 09:32.243
doesn't testify, Harvey.

09:32.245 --> 09:35.046
Or I'll find somebody who can.

09:37.383 --> 09:39.283
I wanna speak to whoever the
hell's in charge of recruiting

09:39.285 --> 09:40.818
and I wanna speak to them now.

09:40.820 --> 09:42.219
Well, I'm afraid
that's not possible.

09:42.221 --> 09:44.021
What do you mean
it's not possible?

09:44.023 --> 09:45.256
I mean you'll have to
make an appointment.

09:45.258 --> 09:46.357
We don't take in walk-ins.

09:46.359 --> 09:47.725
Well, I'm not a walk-in.

09:47.727 --> 09:49.126
My name is Louis Litt,

09:49.128 --> 09:51.062
from the firm
Pearson Specter Litt.

09:51.064 --> 09:52.463
- Wait, you can't go in there.
- Oh, yes I can.

09:52.465 --> 09:54.198
If you people think you can
dismiss our firm,

09:54.200 --> 09:56.200
you have another thing com--

09:58.438 --> 10:03.441
Sheila.
- Louis.

10:03.443 --> 10:05.876
What are you doing here?

10:05.878 --> 10:07.745
Um, uh--well, I've worked
at Columbia

10:07.747 --> 10:09.747
for the past six months.

10:09.749 --> 10:11.415
But you said you would
never leave Harvard.

10:11.417 --> 10:14.418
I did, Louis.

10:14.420 --> 10:17.421
But--
- But what?

10:17.423 --> 10:21.459
My fiancé lives in the city
and I wanted to be with him.

10:21.461 --> 10:24.195
- Fiancé.
- Yes.

10:24.197 --> 10:26.897
We're getting married
in two weeks.

10:26.899 --> 10:29.366
I'm sorry, Louis.
- You don't need to be sorry.

10:31.070 --> 10:33.771
And I understand why you didn't
send the applications over.

10:33.773 --> 10:38.442
You didn't want me to be hurt.
- I didn't.

10:38.444 --> 10:40.144
But now that you know,
there's no reason

10:40.146 --> 10:42.413
to punish you or the firm.

10:42.415 --> 10:44.215
I guess not.

10:44.217 --> 10:46.117
I'll send over our best
and our brightest

10:46.119 --> 10:47.451
and make sure they understand
it's an opportunity

10:47.453 --> 10:52.456
to learn at the foot
of a master.

10:52.458 --> 10:53.858
It's good to see you, Sheila.

10:53.860 --> 10:55.392
Good to see you too, Louis.

10:56.262 --> 11:01.365
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:01.367 --> 11:03.334
Harvey, what happened?
They go for it?

11:03.336 --> 11:05.903
What happened was your
backstabbing father-in-law

11:05.905 --> 11:07.371
blew up the settlement.

11:07.373 --> 11:09.273
- What? Why?
- 'Cause he's an asshole.

11:09.275 --> 11:12.276
Now I gotta stop Gallo
from testifying.

11:12.278 --> 11:14.211
What the hell
are you talking about?

11:14.213 --> 11:16.147
I'm talking about
going to the prison

11:16.149 --> 11:18.249
and convincing
that psychopath not to talk.

11:18.251 --> 11:21.252
- Harvey, that's a bad idea.
- Don't you get it?

11:21.254 --> 11:22.920
He talks, Alex goes down.

11:22.922 --> 11:24.355
That's the whole thing
we're trying to avoid.

11:24.357 --> 11:25.389
I'm not saying
it's a bad idea

11:25.391 --> 11:26.490
to shut Gallo down.

11:26.492 --> 11:28.292
I'm saying that you are not

11:28.294 --> 11:30.194
the one to do it.
- Are you out of your mind?

11:30.196 --> 11:31.896
You're not supposed to be
anywhere near this case.

11:31.898 --> 11:34.965
Reform Corp. gets wind of this--
- And what, Harvey?

11:34.967 --> 11:36.967
I shut down the star witness
on the other side.

11:36.969 --> 11:38.569
They're not gonna be pissed.
They're gonna give me a medal.

11:38.571 --> 11:40.237
What makes you think
you're gonna be better

11:40.239 --> 11:41.906
at that than me?
- Because I might've been

11:41.908 --> 11:43.574
the one who kept him
there longer, but you--

11:43.576 --> 11:45.376
you're the one who put him there
in the first place.

11:45.378 --> 11:48.913
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:51.384 --> 11:52.883
Mm, what are you doing here?

11:52.885 --> 11:55.486
I thought you were off the case.
- I was.

11:55.488 --> 11:57.421
Now I'm back on.

11:57.423 --> 12:00.257
'Cause I need to
give you something.

12:00.259 --> 12:01.559
Yeah, what's this?

12:01.561 --> 12:03.194
It's a hell of a lot more
than whatever

12:03.196 --> 12:04.929
Robert Zane
is paying you to testify.

12:04.931 --> 12:06.397
It's on top of whatever
settlement

12:06.399 --> 12:08.199
your daughter
is still gonna get.

12:08.201 --> 12:09.867
All you have to do
is keep your mouth shut.

12:09.869 --> 12:11.535
Yeah, I'm not interested
in your money.

12:11.537 --> 12:13.337
No, Gallo,
you're not getting me, this--

12:13.339 --> 12:14.872
You're not getting me.
I don't give

12:14.874 --> 12:17.441
a God damn about your money.

12:17.443 --> 12:19.410
Robert Zane already told me
you'd be in here

12:19.412 --> 12:20.978
trying to screw me over.
- I'm not trying

12:20.980 --> 12:22.546
to screw you over.
- Then why have you been

12:22.548 --> 12:24.281
trying to get me to do
the exact opposite thing

12:24.283 --> 12:25.850
for the last month?
- Because--

12:25.852 --> 12:27.518
Because the two of you
don't give a shit

12:27.520 --> 12:30.487
about anything but yourselves.

12:30.489 --> 12:32.489
The situation has changed.

12:32.491 --> 12:34.892
You know what hasn't changed?

12:34.894 --> 12:36.427
Denise.

12:36.429 --> 12:37.995
What she thinks of me.

12:37.997 --> 12:39.563
- Frank, that's--
- See, you came in here

12:39.565 --> 12:41.365
trying to get me
to buy her love back.

12:41.367 --> 12:43.567
I almost did it.

12:43.569 --> 12:47.538
But I can't get anything
from her with just money.

12:47.540 --> 12:49.573
I need her to see me
get up on that stand

12:49.575 --> 12:52.543
admit what I did
and ask for forgiveness.

12:52.545 --> 12:55.312
Robert Zane understands that
because he's got a daughter.

12:55.314 --> 12:57.448
- I understand that--
- No, you don't.

12:57.450 --> 13:01.485
I need her to see me do this.

13:02.622 --> 13:06.290
And nothing you or Harvey
can say is gonna change that.

13:06.292 --> 13:09.894
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:12.132 --> 13:15.033
[both laughing]
- And then you said,

13:15.035 --> 13:16.268
"It's Mr. Dipshit,
thank you very much."

13:16.270 --> 13:17.535
Well, if he's gonna
be a stickler

13:17.537 --> 13:19.337
about what name
is on the reservation,

13:19.339 --> 13:21.139
[laughs] And then for
the rest of the weekend,

13:21.141 --> 13:23.041
we didn't have to pay
for a single drink.

13:23.043 --> 13:25.010
Which was a good thing because
you ordered tequila shots

13:25.012 --> 13:26.011
for everyone in the restaurant.
- It was Cinco de Mayo.

13:26.013 --> 13:27.012
It was August 9th.

13:27.014 --> 13:28.380
[both laugh]

13:28.382 --> 13:30.148
I can't believe
you still remember that.

13:30.150 --> 13:32.083
I remember a lot of things
about those days.

13:32.085 --> 13:34.452
Which is why I can't believe
that there's not a, uh,

13:34.454 --> 13:36.554
a Mr. Donna Paulson yet.
- Well.

13:36.556 --> 13:40.125
You know I have my standards.

13:40.127 --> 13:41.593
Well, I'm glad to see
you haven't lowered them.

13:41.595 --> 13:43.561
To tell you the truth,
I actually raised them.

13:43.563 --> 13:45.363
At least professionally.

13:45.365 --> 13:47.299
You mean you finally
stopped working for Harvey?

13:47.301 --> 13:49.367
Yes and no.

13:49.369 --> 13:52.370
I still work at the firm,
but I'm COO now.

13:52.372 --> 13:55.106
- Donna, that is fantastic.
- It is.

13:55.108 --> 13:56.508
So what about you?

13:56.510 --> 13:58.643
No Mrs. Meadows yet?

13:58.645 --> 14:01.513
Um, actually, I--

14:01.515 --> 14:05.383
I got married
about three years ago.

14:05.385 --> 14:07.085
Mark, if you're married,
why did you

14:07.087 --> 14:08.353
agree to have lunch with me?

14:08.355 --> 14:10.522
Because you called
and you invited me

14:10.524 --> 14:13.158
and--and I thought
it's just lunch, and--

14:13.160 --> 14:15.460
This hasn't felt like just
lunch and you know it.

14:15.462 --> 14:17.329
No, it hasn't.

14:17.331 --> 14:19.364
To tell you the truth,

14:19.366 --> 14:22.567
I think about you all the time.

14:22.569 --> 14:24.469
[sighs] And my wife
and I have been

14:24.471 --> 14:26.438
at each other's throats
for months.

14:26.440 --> 14:28.440
And then you called and
I thought that I would meet you

14:28.442 --> 14:30.241
and just see what happened.

14:30.243 --> 14:32.410
Well, I can tell you
what's not gonna happen.

14:32.412 --> 14:34.679
I'm not gonna be
the answer to your problems.

14:34.681 --> 14:37.649
Well, I'm--I'm so sorry.

14:37.651 --> 14:39.617
Look, I'm not gonna lie

14:39.619 --> 14:42.253
and say that I don't think about
you, too, from time to time.

14:42.255 --> 14:45.190
I do.

14:45.192 --> 14:48.493
But this can't be the way that
things start up again with us.

14:48.495 --> 14:52.163
So if at some point,
you call and you say

14:52.165 --> 14:54.566
that things are over
between you and your wife

14:54.568 --> 14:56.568
and you wanna go out with me,

14:56.570 --> 15:00.372
I'd be open to that.

15:00.374 --> 15:02.707
But I'm not open to this.

15:03.577 --> 15:05.677
I understand.

15:08.348 --> 15:10.648
[sighs]

15:12.586 --> 15:15.153
It was good to see you, Mark.

15:15.155 --> 15:17.489
It's good to see you too,
Donna.

15:24.131 --> 15:26.531
Rachel.

15:26.533 --> 15:28.266
Hey.

15:28.268 --> 15:33.138
You are a sight for sore eyes.
- Am I?

15:33.140 --> 15:35.673
Whoa, what's going on?

15:35.675 --> 15:37.609
Did you have a bad day?
- I was actually

15:37.611 --> 15:39.711
having a great day
until I found out

15:39.713 --> 15:43.748
that the witness in the murder
case is Frank Gallo.

15:45.652 --> 15:47.485
- Rachel, I was gonna--
- Gonna tell me?

15:47.487 --> 15:49.687
When, exactly?
When the whole thing was over?

15:49.689 --> 15:51.489
Because I also found out
that you and Harvey

15:51.491 --> 15:53.224
went to my dad
to keep this thing alive.

15:53.226 --> 15:54.726
- Rachel--
- How many times

15:54.728 --> 15:56.461
do I have to tell you
I can take care of myself?

15:56.463 --> 15:57.762
What did you want me to say?

15:57.764 --> 15:59.631
That I shouldn't have gone
to Gallo?

15:59.633 --> 16:00.765
Or that I shouldn't have taken
this whole thing on

16:00.767 --> 16:02.434
in the first place?

16:02.436 --> 16:04.169
Because I am never
gonna say that.

16:04.171 --> 16:05.703
This has nothing to do with
any of that.

16:05.705 --> 16:07.672
This has to do with you
respecting me as a lawyer.

16:07.674 --> 16:09.407
So you're telling me that if I
had let you in on the plan,

16:09.409 --> 16:11.309
you would've been good
with all of it.

16:11.311 --> 16:13.611
I don't know if I would've
been good with any of it.

16:13.613 --> 16:16.614
What I do know is that you
need to get through your head

16:16.616 --> 16:18.316
that I am a grown woman

16:18.318 --> 16:19.584
and that I am not
a damsel in distress

16:19.586 --> 16:21.519
that needs protecting.

16:21.521 --> 16:27.192
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:34.367 --> 16:38.803
Whatever it is, Donna,
I don't have it in me.

16:38.805 --> 16:41.706
It's okay, Louis. I didn't
even know you were up here.

16:44.344 --> 16:47.512
If you wanna be alone, I can--
- Sheila's getting married.

16:47.514 --> 16:50.281
I'm so sorry.

16:50.283 --> 16:51.549
She didn't wanna tell me
because she thought

16:51.551 --> 16:53.218
I couldn't handle it.

16:55.689 --> 16:57.655
I get it.

16:57.657 --> 17:00.358
Maybe.

17:00.360 --> 17:02.260
But what you don't get is
what it's like

17:02.262 --> 17:03.728
to find out twice in one year

17:03.730 --> 17:05.430
that the person you thought
was the love of your life

17:05.432 --> 17:08.500
doesn't want you.

17:10.470 --> 17:13.738
I understand that
more than you think.

17:13.740 --> 17:15.573
What do you mean?

17:15.575 --> 17:19.644
I had lunch
with an ex-boyfriend today.

17:19.646 --> 17:21.646
Someone I cared a lot about.

17:24.317 --> 17:26.416
I looked him up, wondering if
there was still something there

17:26.419 --> 17:31.222
and while we were eating,
he told me he was married.

17:31.224 --> 17:35.527
Why'd he have lunch with you?

17:35.529 --> 17:37.529
Because, Louis.

17:37.531 --> 17:39.697
People are more complicated
than you think.

17:39.699 --> 17:42.667
Well, it's not complicated
for Sheila.

17:42.669 --> 17:48.840
She's found her man,
and that is that.

17:48.842 --> 17:51.309
Louis, I'm not sure I feel
comfortable leaving you

17:51.311 --> 17:52.610
up here all alone.

17:52.612 --> 17:55.613
It's okay, Donna.
I'm not gonna jump.

17:55.615 --> 17:58.416
Unless you can guarantee me
I can land on Sheila's fiancé.

17:58.418 --> 18:00.518
[chuckles]

18:00.520 --> 18:06.758
Okay.
You're gonna be all right.

18:06.760 --> 18:10.261
But I'm still not leaving
you up here all alone.

18:10.263 --> 18:14.599
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:14.601 --> 18:16.301
Whatever it is,
I don't need to hear it

18:16.303 --> 18:17.635
because I already know
what you're gonna say.

18:17.637 --> 18:19.504
Well, I'm gonna say it anyway.

18:19.506 --> 18:21.506
I didn't bring you this case
to take you to court.

18:21.508 --> 18:24.409
I brought it to you so you
could give these people justice.

18:24.411 --> 18:25.877
Bullshit. You brought it to me

18:25.879 --> 18:27.779
to get you out of hot water.

18:27.781 --> 18:29.614
And I like I already told you,

18:29.616 --> 18:31.382
this is my case.

18:31.384 --> 18:32.917
Don't you dare
tell me how to run it.

18:32.919 --> 18:34.619
I know that Robert, but look,

18:34.621 --> 18:36.788
if you dig too deep,

18:36.790 --> 18:38.523
it's gonna end up
putting one of my own

18:38.525 --> 18:40.425
behind bars for a crime
he didn't commit.

18:40.427 --> 18:43.361
Well, it doesn't take too much
for me to guess who that is.

18:43.363 --> 18:45.730
And I don't give a shit
about Alex Williams.

18:45.732 --> 18:47.632
You know what I do
give a shit about?

18:47.634 --> 18:49.601
The United States is 5%
of the world's population.

18:49.603 --> 18:51.769
But it's got 25%
of its prisoners.

18:51.771 --> 18:52.804
But that's not something
you white guys

18:52.806 --> 18:54.305
want to talk about.

18:54.307 --> 18:55.673
- Robert--
- I grew up

18:55.675 --> 18:57.875
in the roughest part
of Harlem there is.

18:57.877 --> 18:59.544
Nine out of ten kids
on my block

18:59.546 --> 19:01.646
ended up in places like that.

19:01.648 --> 19:05.450
And every day of my life,

19:05.452 --> 19:08.353
I think...

19:08.355 --> 19:11.456
there but by the grace of God.

19:11.458 --> 19:12.790
And they're taking these kids--

19:12.792 --> 19:14.726
like the ones I knew-
and they're

19:14.728 --> 19:17.428
extending their sentences
and murdering some of them.

19:17.430 --> 19:19.764
So no matter what you do
or what you say,

19:19.766 --> 19:22.667
they're going to take my offer
or we're going to trial.

19:22.669 --> 19:25.436
Either way, they're gonna pay.

19:25.438 --> 19:28.806
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

19:28.808 --> 19:32.710
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:32.712 --> 19:34.712
Harvey. I was just about
to call you.

19:34.714 --> 19:36.447
Since you didn't already,

19:36.449 --> 19:37.882
I'm guessing you couldn't
convince Gallo

19:37.884 --> 19:39.751
not to testify.

19:39.753 --> 19:42.487
He doesn't want our money,
Harvey.

19:42.489 --> 19:43.855
He wants his daughter's
forgiveness

19:43.857 --> 19:45.723
and thinks the only way
he's gonna get it

19:45.725 --> 19:47.592
is by testifying.
- Bullshit. He wants something.

19:47.594 --> 19:49.394
We just need to find out
what it is.

19:49.396 --> 19:50.928
Listen to me.
I was in the room with him.

19:50.930 --> 19:53.464
This thing with his daughter
is real.

19:53.466 --> 19:55.767
He's not gonna back down.
- Son of a bitch.

19:55.769 --> 19:57.869
- What are we gonna do now?
- I hate to say it.

19:57.871 --> 20:00.638
We may need to find
some dirt on Zane.

20:00.640 --> 20:02.373
Harvey,
I'm not gonna blackmail

20:02.375 --> 20:03.841
my future father-in-law

20:03.843 --> 20:05.777
about a case that we gave him
to begin with.

20:05.779 --> 20:07.679
You didn't give it to him.
I did.

20:07.681 --> 20:09.681
And I did it to make sure
two things happened,

20:09.683 --> 20:11.516
and one was saving
Alex Williams.

20:11.518 --> 20:12.884
So if you don't wanna
find something on Zane,

20:12.886 --> 20:14.385
I will.

20:14.387 --> 20:16.554
Neither one of you has to.

20:16.556 --> 20:17.689
- Rachel--
- Harvey, I know

20:17.691 --> 20:18.956
how things work.

20:18.958 --> 20:20.458
I meant, you don't have to find

20:20.460 --> 20:21.793
dirt on my father because I know

20:21.795 --> 20:23.861
how to stop Frank Gallo
from testifying.

20:23.863 --> 20:26.864
But my dad isn't gonna be the
only one who doesn't like it.

20:26.866 --> 20:28.700
You two aren't gonna
like it either.

20:28.702 --> 20:30.635
- Why not?
- Because it involves

20:30.637 --> 20:31.669
impugning his integrity

20:31.671 --> 20:33.538
and doing it through me.

20:33.540 --> 20:34.639
If you're saying what I think
you're saying,

20:34.641 --> 20:36.441
that's playing with fire.

20:36.443 --> 20:37.475
And I already told you
I don't have a problem

20:37.477 --> 20:38.876
playing with fire.

20:38.878 --> 20:40.445
My problem is being left out
of the game.

20:40.447 --> 20:41.846
So if my dad has an issue
with it,

20:41.848 --> 20:43.648
you tell him to take it up
with me.

20:47.721 --> 20:49.921
Lewis, that woman from
Columbia University's

20:49.923 --> 20:51.789
on the line again.

20:51.791 --> 20:53.691
She'd like to know what you
thought about her candidate.

20:53.693 --> 20:55.660
Tell her we already
filled the position.

20:55.662 --> 20:58.963
Lewis, tell me
what's going on.

20:58.965 --> 21:01.566
You went all the way over there
to get them on board

21:01.568 --> 21:03.735
and now you're asking me
to lie to this woman.

21:03.737 --> 21:06.671
What's going on is
I don't wanna see her,

21:06.673 --> 21:10.408
I don't wanna talk to her,
I don't wanna hear her name.

21:10.410 --> 21:12.677
So if you don't wanna lie,
then don't.

21:12.679 --> 21:14.912
But I am not taking that call.

21:19.386 --> 21:21.719
Look, Mike,
Rachel's plan could work,

21:21.721 --> 21:23.654
but it's gonna piss Zane off
and you know it.

21:23.656 --> 21:25.123
Not to mention what
it's gonna do to Gallo.

21:25.125 --> 21:26.958
Rachel and I can take care
of the fallout, trust me.

21:26.960 --> 21:28.693
Before you got there last night,

21:28.695 --> 21:30.395
she made it clear
that she can handle herself.

21:30.397 --> 21:32.797
Yeah, I don't care
what she thinks she can handle.

21:32.799 --> 21:34.599
I'm not doing it.
- Then what exactly

21:34.601 --> 21:36.634
is your plan, because the
hearing's in five minutes

21:36.636 --> 21:38.603
and we don't have another way
to stop Gallo from testifying.

21:38.605 --> 21:40.004
What the hell
are you doing here, Bratton?

21:40.006 --> 21:41.839
I'm to make sure
you're doing your job.

21:41.841 --> 21:43.174
Bullshit,
I don't work for you.

21:43.176 --> 21:45.042
I didn't say you did.
But if you can't

21:45.044 --> 21:46.944
make this thing go away,
you're not gonna be working

21:46.946 --> 21:49.847
for Reform Corp. or
Masterson Construction either.

21:49.849 --> 21:52.683
- Is that a fact?
- Sure as hell is.

21:52.685 --> 21:55.153
You don't stop our prison friend
from testifying,

21:55.155 --> 21:56.854
I'm gonna take this thing over

21:56.856 --> 21:58.790
and the first thing
I'm going to do

21:58.792 --> 22:01.092
is offer up a sacrificial lamb

22:01.094 --> 22:02.660
named Alex Williams.

22:02.662 --> 22:08.966
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:08.968 --> 22:12.069
How do you feel
about Rachel's plan now?

22:13.740 --> 22:15.440
Gentlemen, this is
the second time

22:15.442 --> 22:17.675
the issue of Frank Gallo's
come up in this case.

22:17.677 --> 22:19.143
What is it this time?
- What it is, Your Honor,

22:19.145 --> 22:21.012
is Mr. Specter knows
Mr. Gallo is gonna

22:21.014 --> 22:22.747
take him out at the knees

22:22.749 --> 22:24.148
and he's gonna do
anything he can to stop him.

22:24.150 --> 22:26.717
I'll do anything I can
because Frank Gallo

22:26.719 --> 22:29.887
is about to commit perjury
and Robert Zane knows it.

22:29.889 --> 22:31.789
You accuse someone of
something like that

22:31.791 --> 22:33.991
in an open court, you better
damn well have proof.

22:33.993 --> 22:35.126
Mr. Zane, watch yourself.

22:35.128 --> 22:36.894
And Mr. Specter, he's right.

22:36.896 --> 22:38.463
I know that, Your Honor.

22:38.465 --> 22:40.731
Which is why I have proof
right here.

22:40.733 --> 22:42.233
And what is that?

22:42.235 --> 22:45.203
Pictures of Rachel Zane
sent by Frank Gallo

22:45.205 --> 22:47.905
designed to intimidate her
father into suborning perjury.

22:47.907 --> 22:49.207
That is a lie!

22:49.209 --> 22:50.942
Whatever's in that envelope
is bullshit.

22:50.944 --> 22:52.877
Mr. Zane, I'm going
to let that language go

22:52.879 --> 22:54.779
and I don't want to
accuse you of anything,

22:54.781 --> 22:57.048
but these photos do indicate
that a known criminal

22:57.050 --> 22:58.816
is threatening your daughter.

22:58.818 --> 23:00.184
I don't give a shit
what they indicate.

23:00.186 --> 23:01.686
I've never seen them before
in my life

23:01.688 --> 23:03.054
and I don't suborn perjury.

23:03.056 --> 23:04.789
- That's enough.
- I don't know

23:04.791 --> 23:05.857
what's going on here,
but until I get

23:05.859 --> 23:07.024
to the bottom of this,

23:07.026 --> 23:09.260
Frank Gallo is not testifying.

23:11.698 --> 23:13.998
You son of a bitch.
You used my daughter against me.

23:14.000 --> 23:15.700
I'm gonna God damn
knock you out.

23:15.702 --> 23:17.235
Robert, don't you come at me.

23:17.237 --> 23:18.970
You don't want me
coming at you because you know

23:18.972 --> 23:20.705
once I got my hands on you
you're done!

23:20.707 --> 23:22.173
Which is why I'll drop you
before you do.

23:22.175 --> 23:24.108
- Go ahead and drop me!
- Robert.

23:24.110 --> 23:25.810
You're not gonna throw a punch
because you know you're wrong.

23:25.812 --> 23:27.245
Robert, Robert!
Hey, Robert, Robert! Stop!

23:27.247 --> 23:30.014
It was Rachel's idea.

23:30.016 --> 23:31.782
- What did you just say?
- Harvey didn't even

23:31.784 --> 23:33.718
wanna do it.
- Bullshit, it was her idea.

23:33.720 --> 23:35.953
Robert, she's a grown woman,
she made a decision.

23:35.955 --> 23:37.755
You don't believe me,
you can ask her yourself.

23:37.757 --> 23:39.223
But I'm telling you,
you wanna be angry at someone,

23:39.225 --> 23:41.259
do not take it out on Harvey.
- I don't care

23:41.261 --> 23:42.860
whose idea it was.

23:42.862 --> 23:44.729
You used her to slander me!

23:44.731 --> 23:47.198
In open court!

23:47.200 --> 23:48.966
You should be ashamed
of yourself.

23:48.968 --> 23:53.104
And you--you tell your
Reform Corp. buddies

23:53.106 --> 23:55.907
that Frank Gallo is gonna
take that stand

23:55.909 --> 23:57.575
one way or another.

23:57.577 --> 24:01.178
And there's nothing
they can do to stop it.

24:01.180 --> 24:04.181
<i>[tense music]</i>

24:04.183 --> 24:06.751
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:06.753 --> 24:07.818
[phone buzzing]

24:10.256 --> 24:14.125
- Mark, hi.
- Hey, um,

24:14.127 --> 24:15.860
I hope I'm not interrupting.

24:15.862 --> 24:18.296
No, actually, I'm just, um--

24:18.298 --> 24:20.965
I'm just finishing up
for the night.

24:23.303 --> 24:24.936
Are you still there?

24:24.938 --> 24:26.871
Yeah, um--

24:26.873 --> 24:29.040
Sorry, um, I'm just--

24:29.042 --> 24:31.075
- Mark.
- Hold on, please, Donna.

24:31.077 --> 24:33.811
Let me just--
let me just get this out.

24:33.813 --> 24:37.582
<i>Seeing you the other day</i>
<i>brought up a lot of feelings.</i>

24:37.584 --> 24:40.818
It did for me, too.
But you're married.

24:40.820 --> 24:43.888
- Not happily.
- Mark--

24:43.890 --> 24:45.823
The thing is, I walked away
from you once before.

24:45.825 --> 24:49.293
And ever since...

24:49.295 --> 24:52.363
I--I wonder what would've
happened if I hadn't--

24:52.365 --> 24:57.902
<i>I just--I can't walk away</i>
<i>from you again.</i>

24:57.904 --> 24:59.971
What are you saying?

24:59.973 --> 25:02.373
<i>My office is hosting</i>
<i>a conference this week</i>

25:02.375 --> 25:05.109
and everyone's staying
in the city, so...

25:05.111 --> 25:08.379
I'm not going back
to Connecticut until Saturday.

25:10.049 --> 25:13.250
I'd like to see you
before I do.

25:13.252 --> 25:17.154
What am I supposed
to say to that?

25:17.156 --> 25:19.190
You don't have to
say anything.

25:19.192 --> 25:20.958
<i>But I just wanted you to know</i>

25:20.960 --> 25:22.393
<i>that I'll be staying</i>
<i>at the Carlyle</i>

25:22.395 --> 25:24.028
<i>for the next two nights.</i>

25:24.030 --> 25:26.063
<i>Room 508.</i>

25:26.065 --> 25:28.332
What about your wife?

25:28.334 --> 25:31.068
I don't know how
I'm gonna handle that.

25:31.070 --> 25:33.971
And I definitely won't be able
to handle it by tomorrow.

25:33.973 --> 25:37.908
<i>So if you don't wanna see me,</i>
<i>I'll understand.</i>

25:37.910 --> 25:40.645
But I had to call.

25:40.647 --> 25:43.014
<i>Good night, Donna.</i>

25:43.016 --> 25:45.383
Good night, Mark.

25:52.959 --> 25:56.027
[phone ringing]

25:58.965 --> 26:01.132
Gretchen, I told you
I'm not taking any calls.

26:01.134 --> 26:03.067
<i>Louis?</i>

26:03.069 --> 26:05.102
Sheila. You called
my private line.

26:05.104 --> 26:06.971
Is this a bad time?

26:06.973 --> 26:08.973
I wouldn't say
it's a great time.

26:08.975 --> 26:10.908
Louis, I lied
when I said I didn't tell you

26:10.910 --> 26:13.277
about being at Columbia
because I didn't wanna hurt you.

26:13.279 --> 26:15.279
Well, then why
didn't you tell me?

26:15.281 --> 26:16.981
<i>Because I haven't gotten you</i>
<i>out of my system.</i>

26:16.983 --> 26:18.382
<i>And when I say that,</i>

26:18.384 --> 26:23.087
what I'm really saying is,
Louis,

26:23.089 --> 26:27.258
I want your body one last time
before I walk down that aisle.

26:27.260 --> 26:28.392
Say what, now?

26:28.394 --> 26:30.461
I wanna devour every inch

26:30.463 --> 26:32.396
of your flesh.

26:32.398 --> 26:35.032
I want you to rock my world
six ways from Sunday.

26:35.034 --> 26:36.200
<i>I want to--</i>
I think I get the--

26:36.202 --> 26:38.002
<i>Do not interrupt me!</i>

26:38.004 --> 26:39.737
Because I demand a travel
to the moon and back

26:39.739 --> 26:41.739
seven to nine more times

26:41.741 --> 26:46.444
in one life-shattering
12-36 hour period.

26:46.446 --> 26:48.279
- Oh, my God.
- That's when I plan on

26:48.281 --> 26:52.216
making you scream until
you can't scream anymore.

26:52.218 --> 26:54.051
Sheila, where is this
coming from?

26:54.053 --> 26:55.953
<i>You know exactly</i>
<i>where it's coming from.</i>

26:55.955 --> 26:57.354
It started the second
you strutted into my office

26:57.356 --> 26:59.090
like a Viking god,

26:59.092 --> 27:01.192
<i>ready to pillage</i>
<i>a helpless maiden.</i>

27:01.194 --> 27:02.760
I was just coming in
to check on the candidates.

27:02.762 --> 27:04.061
I didn't even know
that you were--

27:04.063 --> 27:05.362
That's what makes it so hot.

27:05.364 --> 27:07.131
Shirley, even though
this image

27:07.133 --> 27:10.367
is making my Viking mast
unfurl to full sail,

27:10.369 --> 27:12.436
I don't think what you're
suggesting is a good idea.

27:12.438 --> 27:14.271
Well, that's because
I haven't told you

27:14.273 --> 27:16.107
that I'm finally gonna let you
do that thing

27:16.109 --> 27:19.176
that you always wanted to do.

27:19.178 --> 27:20.311
- Even the--
- Yes.

27:20.313 --> 27:21.445
- And with the--
- Yes.

27:21.447 --> 27:23.114
And what about the accent?

27:23.116 --> 27:24.315
Oh, with all the accents,
Louis.

27:24.317 --> 27:26.951
With all the accents.

27:26.953 --> 27:28.185
- What about the lisp?
- No.

27:28.187 --> 27:30.154
Ahh! Sheila, I can't!

27:30.156 --> 27:32.056
I respect your integrity,
Louis.

27:32.058 --> 27:33.991
But not enough to stop me
from waiting

27:33.993 --> 27:37.762
for you tomorrow night
in our old hotel suite.

27:37.764 --> 27:39.797
The War Room?

27:39.799 --> 27:42.533
The very one. Ah.

27:42.535 --> 27:46.070
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:46.072 --> 27:48.339
Louis, you've gotta come down
to the bullpen for a second.

27:48.341 --> 27:49.473
You're not gonna believe what
Brian cooked up

27:49.475 --> 27:51.208
for the Langston settlement.

27:51.210 --> 27:52.476
- I can't right now, Rachel.
- Why not?

27:52.478 --> 27:55.446
It's only going to take
a second.

27:55.448 --> 27:57.314
Because I'm not getting up
right now, Rachel,

27:57.316 --> 27:59.083
and there's nothing you can say
to change that.

27:59.085 --> 28:03.087
Louis, what's going on?

28:03.089 --> 28:06.123
Just got off the phone
with Sheila.

28:06.125 --> 28:10.795
She's getting married and she
wants to have one last fling

28:10.797 --> 28:13.097
before she goes down the aisle.

28:13.099 --> 28:16.367
And you don't
wanna do that because

28:16.369 --> 28:18.369
you don't wanna be
that kind of person.

28:18.371 --> 28:20.805
- No, I don't.
- So then what's the problem?

28:20.807 --> 28:24.175
The problem is--is...

28:24.177 --> 28:26.243
I haven't had anything
go my way in so long,

28:26.245 --> 28:28.412
I can't even remember
what that's like.

28:28.414 --> 28:30.347
And I could really
use a night where

28:30.349 --> 28:36.287
I can forget my pain
and feel good about myself.

28:36.289 --> 28:39.323
Louis, I can't tell you
what the answer is

28:39.325 --> 28:40.558
because it's not a small thing

28:40.560 --> 28:42.293
to do something like that.

28:42.295 --> 28:45.296
But if it helps,
I know you have a good heart.

28:45.298 --> 28:48.365
So whatever you decide,
it's not gonna change

28:48.367 --> 28:50.601
how I feel about you.

28:50.603 --> 28:52.536
Thanks, Rachel.

28:52.538 --> 28:55.539
<i>[somber music]</i>

28:55.541 --> 28:59.243
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:07.421 --> 29:10.356
What are you doing here,
Counselor?

29:10.358 --> 29:11.890
I'm here because I have
relevant information

29:11.892 --> 29:13.592
on the Reform Corp. matter.
- And if that's the case,

29:13.594 --> 29:15.361
you should be
doing it in chambers

29:15.363 --> 29:16.628
and Robert Zane should be there.
- Your Honor,

29:16.630 --> 29:18.464
Robert Zane's not
in his right mind.

29:18.466 --> 29:19.865
You saw what happened
to him yesterday

29:19.867 --> 29:21.967
and that's why before you rule
on Frank Gallo--

29:21.969 --> 29:24.470
- Stop right there, Mr. Specter.
- No, I'm not gonna stop there.

29:24.472 --> 29:25.504
- Yes, you are.
- Your Honor--

29:25.506 --> 29:27.673
Frank Gallo is dead.

29:27.675 --> 29:28.941
- What?
- He was murdered

29:28.943 --> 29:30.843
in his cell last night.

29:30.845 --> 29:32.611
So whatever it was
that you were going

29:32.613 --> 29:33.846
to say about
him is irrelevant.

29:33.848 --> 29:35.614
The man can't testify.

29:35.616 --> 29:38.884
So I think it's time
to let him rest in peace.

29:38.886 --> 29:45.624
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:48.896 --> 29:50.662
Donna.

29:50.664 --> 29:52.598
How long have you
been standing there?

29:52.600 --> 29:54.800
I was just walking by
and I didn't recognize you.

29:54.802 --> 29:56.602
And you thought,
who is that strange woman

29:56.604 --> 29:57.770
in Harvey's office?

29:57.772 --> 29:59.838
That's not what I thought.

30:01.609 --> 30:03.776
Have you seen Harvey,
by any chance?

30:03.778 --> 30:05.644
He's actually out
for the rest of the day.

30:05.646 --> 30:08.046
That's okay.
I'll just see him tonight.

30:09.784 --> 30:11.950
Oh, I get it.

30:11.952 --> 30:13.652
You stopped by to surprise him

30:13.654 --> 30:16.922
because it's your
two month anniversary.

30:16.924 --> 30:20.726
- How can you know that?
- Because I care about him.

30:20.728 --> 30:23.896
And you coming into his life...

30:23.898 --> 30:25.764
is a memorable event.

30:27.902 --> 30:30.636
Well, it was good
to see you, Donna.

30:33.574 --> 30:37.910
[sighs] Carbone.

30:37.912 --> 30:39.511
I'm sorry.

30:39.513 --> 30:40.813
It's a hole in the wall,

30:40.815 --> 30:42.448
but it's one
of Harvey's favorite places.

30:42.450 --> 30:44.516
So if you're looking
for a reservation--

30:44.518 --> 30:46.885
Actually, I already have one.

30:46.887 --> 30:48.554
Oh, let me guess.

30:48.556 --> 30:51.056
At Carbone.
- Yes.

30:51.058 --> 30:53.459
Well, I'm sure
you'll have a great time.

30:53.461 --> 30:56.028
Thank you for
the recommendation, Donna.

31:00.568 --> 31:03.535
There you are. I've been
looking all over for you.

31:03.537 --> 31:05.971
- What is it, Rachel?
- Okay, I was thinking,

31:05.973 --> 31:08.507
we never got to have
those drinks we talked about

31:08.509 --> 31:09.741
and, Donna, I know you've been
going through

31:09.743 --> 31:11.543
a lot of stuff, lately.

31:11.545 --> 31:13.579
So I thought maybe
you could use a night

31:13.581 --> 31:15.614
where you just
lose your troubles

31:15.616 --> 31:18.784
and just feel good
about yourself.

31:18.786 --> 31:20.853
- I could.
- So, what do you say?

31:20.855 --> 31:22.588
Is Harriet Specter available

31:22.590 --> 31:26.592
to go out with
Michelle Ross tonight?

31:26.594 --> 31:29.895
I can't tonight,
Rachel; I have plans.

31:29.897 --> 31:32.965
That's mysterious.
What do you have, a hot date?

31:32.967 --> 31:35.701
Yeah.
Something like that.

31:38.606 --> 31:40.138
- Is he in?
- Yes, but you can't

31:40.140 --> 31:41.807
go in there.
- Try and stop me.

31:41.809 --> 31:44.109
- Wait a second.
- You son of a bitch.

31:44.111 --> 31:46.945
You murdered Frank Gallo.

31:46.947 --> 31:49.014
Ashley, I'll handle this.

31:51.519 --> 31:54.520
I have no idea
what you're talking about.

31:54.522 --> 31:55.921
Bullshit!
You said if I couldn't

31:55.923 --> 31:57.623
stop him from testifying,

31:57.625 --> 31:58.991
you'd find someone who could.

31:58.993 --> 32:00.993
I meant I'd get
Thomas Bratton involved.

32:00.995 --> 32:02.761
I didn't mean I'd kill a man.

32:02.763 --> 32:04.763
And you did stop Gallo
from testifying,

32:04.765 --> 32:06.164
so why would it matter?

32:06.166 --> 32:07.833
Because he wanted to make sure
that Robert Zane

32:07.835 --> 32:09.768
didn't reverse it,
so you had him murdered.

32:09.770 --> 32:12.905
And how exactly did I arrange
this supposed murder?

32:12.907 --> 32:15.674
The same damn way you killed
that guard and covered it up.

32:15.676 --> 32:18.744
Once again, Harvey, I have no
idea what you're talking about.

32:18.746 --> 32:20.712
And you can accuse me
of anything you want,

32:20.714 --> 32:22.614
but that man was
a hardened criminal

32:22.616 --> 32:25.684
who could've been killed
by anyone for anything.

32:25.686 --> 32:28.787
And I am not gonna lose
a second of sleep over it.

32:28.789 --> 32:30.856
I beg to differ.

32:30.858 --> 32:32.658
- Robert.
- What the hell

32:32.660 --> 32:35.994
is going on here?
- I'll tell you what's going on.

32:35.996 --> 32:39.765
I got something
for you to see.

32:39.767 --> 32:42.634
And it's not on Netflix.

32:42.636 --> 32:45.938
Frank Gallo,
prisoner 09842.

32:45.940 --> 32:48.073
Danbury Federal Prison.

32:48.075 --> 32:49.808
All right.
Enough bullshit.

32:49.810 --> 32:52.778
I'm your lawyer.
None of this is admissible.

32:52.780 --> 32:54.613
Now tell me the truth,

32:54.615 --> 32:57.115
so I know what I'm dealing with.

32:57.117 --> 32:59.985
All right, you want the truth,
let's just get to it.

32:59.987 --> 33:04.089
There was a guard, sent a letter
to some lawyer on the outside

33:04.091 --> 33:07.693
who was getting suspicious of
what was going on in there.

33:07.695 --> 33:08.994
They wanted me to remind him

33:08.996 --> 33:10.829
of where he was
in the food chain.

33:10.831 --> 33:14.600
- And you were happy to do it.
- No, I wasn't.

33:14.602 --> 33:16.234
We were hard men in there.

33:16.236 --> 33:18.770
Tough guys, murderers.

33:18.772 --> 33:21.840
That guard was just
a sweet, old man.

33:21.842 --> 33:24.009
Never hurt a soul
in all his years.

33:24.011 --> 33:25.777
And you expect me
to believe all that.

33:25.779 --> 33:28.113
You can believe it or not,
it's the truth.

33:28.115 --> 33:30.115
So I told them I wouldn't do it

33:30.117 --> 33:32.651
until whoever was
running the show

33:32.653 --> 33:34.019
came to me directly.

33:34.021 --> 33:35.120
And they made that happen.

33:35.122 --> 33:36.622
They had no choice.

33:36.624 --> 33:37.689
Next day, the guy showed up

33:37.691 --> 33:38.857
right in my God damn cell

33:38.859 --> 33:40.659
like he owned the place,

33:40.661 --> 33:42.861
which he did.
- And who exactly was that?

33:42.863 --> 33:46.932
Roger Shapiro.
CEO of Reform Corp.

33:47.234 --> 33:48.734
<i>And then what happened?</i>

33:48.736 --> 33:50.802
<i>I, uh--</i>

33:50.804 --> 33:53.872
<i>I got him alone that night</i>
<i>in the mess hall.</i>

33:53.874 --> 33:56.008
Wouldn't you know, the old man
still had some fight in him.

33:56.010 --> 33:58.877
Next thing I knew,
it was him or me, so--

33:58.879 --> 34:00.812
I had to put him down.

34:00.814 --> 34:03.849
You killed him.

34:03.851 --> 34:06.051
Yeah.

34:06.053 --> 34:08.152
I killed him.

34:08.155 --> 34:09.987
And then what did you do?

34:09.989 --> 34:14.025
I told them I was done, out,
no more.

34:14.027 --> 34:17.161
<i>Next night, Roger Shapiro</i>
<i>sent five of my friends</i>

34:17.164 --> 34:20.297
<i>to do the same thing to me.</i>

34:20.300 --> 34:22.833
Looks like you're in
some deep shit, Roger.

34:22.835 --> 34:24.202
I don't believe it.
So you two

34:24.204 --> 34:26.772
were in on this together.
- To quote you,

34:26.774 --> 34:29.041
I have no idea what
you're talking about.

34:29.043 --> 34:31.710
I certainly didn't go to
Robert's house this morning

34:31.712 --> 34:34.813
and tell him that I think that
you had Frank Gallo murdered

34:34.815 --> 34:36.181
So he wouldn't be able
to testify.

34:36.183 --> 34:38.016
And I certainly didn't say
if you had,

34:38.018 --> 34:40.819
you made a huge mistake
because now this tape

34:40.821 --> 34:42.020
is a death bed confession

34:42.022 --> 34:44.089
and by law is admissible.

34:44.091 --> 34:45.924
And all that bullshit
I came up with,

34:45.926 --> 34:48.293
about Robert being intimidated
by Frank Gallo,

34:48.295 --> 34:50.128
well, that doesn't apply anymore

34:50.130 --> 34:53.031
because Frank Gallo's dead.

34:53.033 --> 34:55.701
- So what do you want?
- What I want

34:55.703 --> 34:59.004
is for you to go away
for murder.

34:59.006 --> 35:01.073
But that's not gonna happen

35:01.075 --> 35:03.742
so I'll settle for the number
I wanted in the first place.

35:03.744 --> 35:06.211
But you're never gonna pull
this shit again on prisoners

35:06.213 --> 35:09.948
because if you do, I don't care
about Alex Williams.

35:09.950 --> 35:11.717
This tape goes
to the Department of Justice

35:11.719 --> 35:15.053
and you are headed
to one of your own prisons,

35:15.055 --> 35:16.755
five seconds later.

35:25.833 --> 35:28.233
I think that's something
that I could work with.

35:30.104 --> 35:33.038
Now, if there's nothing else,
I'd like you both to leave.

35:33.040 --> 35:34.906
Oh, we're not done
with you yet.

35:34.908 --> 35:36.808
- What now?
- I'll tell you what now,

35:36.810 --> 35:38.110
you're gonna write up
something for me

35:38.112 --> 35:40.011
and you're not gonna like it.

35:40.013 --> 35:41.346
But if you wanna
stay out of prison,

35:41.348 --> 35:43.014
you're gonna make damn sure

35:43.016 --> 35:44.883
it says exactly
what I need it to.

35:53.260 --> 35:55.160
What the hell is this?

35:55.162 --> 35:57.095
Tommy.

35:57.097 --> 35:59.164
You mind telling me
how the hell you got in here?

35:59.166 --> 36:01.133
People like me here, Tommy.

36:01.135 --> 36:03.001
That's how I got in.

36:03.003 --> 36:06.171
But the question you should be
asking is why I'm here.

36:06.173 --> 36:07.906
I don't give a shit
why you're here.

36:07.908 --> 36:09.341
I want my God damn
affidavit back.

36:09.343 --> 36:11.376
Sure thing. You also want me
to sign over

36:11.378 --> 36:13.545
the deed to my house in
the Hamptons, while I'm at it?

36:13.547 --> 36:15.947
You can keep
your shitty house.

36:15.949 --> 36:17.249
Because you're gonna need
someplace to go

36:17.251 --> 36:19.317
after you resign.
- What did you just say to me?

36:19.319 --> 36:21.319
He said he's here
for his affidavit

36:21.321 --> 36:24.156
and your resignation,
you smug piece of shit.

36:24.158 --> 36:26.491
[laughs] What you guys,
plan on beating it out of me?

36:26.493 --> 36:28.426
Because that's the only way
you'd get it.

36:28.428 --> 36:31.096
We don't need to
beat up an old man, Tommy.

36:31.098 --> 36:34.099
We just need to show you this.

36:34.101 --> 36:36.468
- What's that?
- That's a signed confession

36:36.470 --> 36:39.204
from Robert Shapiro,
say he entered into a conspiracy

36:39.206 --> 36:41.339
with Masterson Construction
to defraud

36:41.341 --> 36:43.074
the United States government.

36:43.076 --> 36:46.511
And that that conspiracy
was arranged by you.

36:46.513 --> 36:49.447
No way.
Roger would never do that.

36:49.449 --> 36:51.550
Oh, he did it.
For the same reason

36:51.552 --> 36:53.552
you're gonna give us
what we want.

36:53.554 --> 36:55.253
We had him by the balls.

36:55.255 --> 36:57.122
Just like I got you
right now, Tommy.

36:57.124 --> 36:59.224
So you can pick up the phone
and call him,

36:59.226 --> 37:02.093
or you can look at my face
and see I'm not lying.

37:02.095 --> 37:04.429
But either way,
we're not leaving here

37:04.431 --> 37:06.031
without getting what we want.

37:10.370 --> 37:12.504
[laughs] I'm not going
to stand here

37:12.506 --> 37:16.107
and write my resignation letter
in front of you two, okay?

37:16.109 --> 37:18.510
Then it's a good thing
we wrote one up for you.

37:18.512 --> 37:21.513
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

37:21.515 --> 37:25.584
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:27.487 --> 37:29.487
By the way, remember when
I told you you owed me?

37:29.489 --> 37:31.389
I'd pretty much
say we're even.

37:31.391 --> 37:34.025
I don't think this word even
means what you think it means.

37:34.027 --> 37:35.360
Oh, well, is that a fact?

37:35.362 --> 37:38.096
You're damn right it is.
I turned down a job offer.

37:38.098 --> 37:39.264
You were gonna go to prison.

37:39.266 --> 37:40.632
You owe me for the rest
of your life.

37:40.634 --> 37:42.534
Got it. Me and you, square.

37:42.536 --> 37:45.003
Once again, I don't think
the word square

37:45.005 --> 37:46.438
means what you think it means.
- You're right.

37:46.440 --> 37:48.306
We still gotta go eat on you.

37:48.308 --> 37:51.076
Sorry, can't tonight, Alex.
I got other plans.

37:55.115 --> 37:56.381
What are you doing here?

37:56.383 --> 37:58.450
I came to apologize
for what I did.

37:58.452 --> 38:00.452
I thought you said
it was Rachel's idea.

38:00.454 --> 38:02.420
It was, but you said

38:02.422 --> 38:03.421
I should've stopped it

38:03.423 --> 38:07.292
in its tracks
and you were right.

38:07.294 --> 38:09.127
Robert, I'm sorry.

38:09.129 --> 38:11.296
I love Rachel. I would never
do anything to hurt her.

38:11.298 --> 38:14.232
But I should've known to never
do anything to hurt you.

38:14.234 --> 38:17.202
It takes a big man
to say that, Mike.

38:17.204 --> 38:20.038
I appreciate it.

38:20.040 --> 38:21.473
And I'd be lying if I didn't
admit it worked out

38:21.475 --> 38:23.642
for everybody in the end.

38:23.644 --> 38:26.177
Yeah, not everybody.

38:26.179 --> 38:28.580
I'm not losing any sleep
over that son of a bitch.

38:28.582 --> 38:31.116
He may not have threatened
Rachel to me,

38:31.118 --> 38:32.317
but he sure as hell
threatened her to you.

38:32.319 --> 38:35.220
I know.
And I know he was a murderer.

38:35.222 --> 38:38.657
But Harvey showed me that
tape.

38:38.659 --> 38:41.326
You can see how much he cared
about his daughter.

38:41.328 --> 38:43.094
Fact of the matter is,

38:43.096 --> 38:47.465
they're never gonna see
each other again.

38:47.467 --> 38:51.269
Then to Frank Gallo.

38:51.271 --> 38:52.671
May he rest in peace.

38:56.076 --> 38:58.610
<i>I told them I was done.</i>
<i>No more, out.</i>

38:58.612 --> 39:01.179
Next night, Roger Shapiro
sent five of my friends

39:01.181 --> 39:02.580
<i>to do the same thing to me.</i>

39:05.519 --> 39:07.619
You're willing to testify
to that in court.

39:07.621 --> 39:10.722
No way, I tell them that,
they'll put me away for murder.

39:10.724 --> 39:13.625
- You're already away.
- Yeah, for seven more years.

39:13.627 --> 39:15.727
I tell them this,
they'll put me away for life.

39:15.729 --> 39:17.362
What if I can
get you immunity?

39:17.364 --> 39:19.364
- You can't promise me that.
- No, I can't.

39:19.366 --> 39:22.233
But if you did this for me,
there's no way

39:22.235 --> 39:24.302
I'm gonna let them
convict you for murder.

39:24.304 --> 39:26.638
Why should I believe you?

39:26.640 --> 39:29.240
For the same reason you need
to take that stand.

39:29.242 --> 39:30.709
I know what it's like
to have a daughter.

39:30.711 --> 39:33.144
<i>And I know you cut that deal</i>
<i>with Mike Ross</i>

39:33.146 --> 39:34.646
<i>so that she'd forgive you.</i>

39:34.648 --> 39:37.515
<i>But she needs more than that</i>
<i>to forgive you.</i>

39:37.517 --> 39:40.685
She needs to know her father
is a good man.

39:40.687 --> 39:43.588
- I'm not a good man.
- Yeah, maybe not.

39:43.590 --> 39:47.425
But if you got up there
and told the world what you did,

39:47.427 --> 39:49.661
<i>and stopped these monsters from</i>
<i>ever doing it again--</i>

39:49.663 --> 39:52.397
<i>you let her see that--</i>
<i>she'll forgive you.</i>

39:52.399 --> 39:54.733
<i>And I swear</i>
<i>on my own daughter,</i>

39:54.735 --> 39:57.235
<i>I will not let you</i>
<i>go down for it.</i>

40:03.310 --> 40:07.178
Okay.

40:07.180 --> 40:11.383
I'll do it.

40:11.385 --> 40:12.550
Denise Gallo?

40:12.552 --> 40:14.452
Who are you?

40:14.454 --> 40:16.421
Someone who knew your father.

40:16.423 --> 40:20.725
He, uh, wanted you to have this.

40:22.429 --> 40:25.196
I want you to know,

40:25.198 --> 40:27.665
he was a decent man.

40:27.667 --> 40:34.305
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:38.578 --> 40:39.577
I believe I just figured out

40:39.579 --> 40:42.547
why you fancy
this place so much.

40:42.549 --> 40:45.617
- Why's that?
- Colors and the candle light.

40:45.619 --> 40:47.585
They make you look
tremendously handsome.

40:47.587 --> 40:49.421
Dr. Agard,
if I didn't know better,

40:49.423 --> 40:50.822
I'd think you were
hitting on me.

40:50.824 --> 40:52.323
If you didn't know better,

40:52.325 --> 40:54.325
I never would've
gotten the chance.

40:59.599 --> 41:01.299
- What's that?
- It's just a little something

41:01.301 --> 41:03.835
I saw that made me
think of you.

41:03.837 --> 41:06.571
And--
- And what?

41:06.573 --> 41:08.506
It's our two month
anniversary.

41:08.508 --> 41:09.741
I didn't want to make
a big deal out of it.

41:09.743 --> 41:11.209
And I certainly
don't expect you to

41:11.211 --> 41:13.611
to have remembered, but--
- Paula, of course I remembered.

41:13.613 --> 41:17.248
Why do you think
I got you this?

41:17.617 --> 41:19.484
That's the key
to your apartment.

41:19.486 --> 41:21.753
Yes, it is.

41:21.755 --> 41:25.390
This is incredibly sweet.

41:25.392 --> 41:26.791
But it isn't gonna fool me
into believing

41:26.793 --> 41:28.626
that you had the faintest notion

41:28.628 --> 41:30.562
it was our two month
anniversary.

41:30.564 --> 41:35.700
You're right. I didn't. But...

41:35.702 --> 41:38.603
I was gonna give you
these tonight, anyway.

41:38.605 --> 41:43.241
Which, if you think about it,

41:43.243 --> 41:44.742
makes it even more special.

41:47.747 --> 41:50.381
Happy anniversary, Paula.

41:50.383 --> 41:52.317
Happy anniversary, Harvey.

41:52.319 --> 41:59.290
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:43.703 --> 42:50.708
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:08.361 --> 43:10.828
[phone buzzing]

43:20.974 --> 43:24.943
I--I didn't know
if you'd come.

43:27.714 --> 43:31.349
I'm sorry, Mark.

43:31.351 --> 43:32.717
I can't do this.

43:32.719 --> 43:34.919
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:34.921 --> 43:36.888
<i>[knocking at door]</i>

43:40.627 --> 43:46.631
I didn't know if you'd come.

43:46.633 --> 43:48.600
How could I not?

